# Project Structure & Architecture

## Overview
This is a React Native/Expo project using TypeScript, Tamagui, and atomic design principles.

## Directory Structure
- `src/frontend/` - Frontend components and logic
- `src/backend/` - Backend utilities and services  
- `src/shared/` - Shared utilities, hooks, and constants
- `app/` - Expo Router app directory (active)
- `src/frontend/app/` - Source version (reference only)

## Atomic Design Architecture
Components are organized using atomic design methodology:
- `src/frontend/components/atoms/` - Basic building blocks (Button, Input, LanguageSelector)
- `src/frontend/components/molecules/` - Component combinations (LoginForm)
- `src/frontend/components/organisms/` - Complex component sections
- `src/frontend/components/templates/` - Page layouts
- `src/frontend/components/pages/` - Complete pages

## Key Configuration Files
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript configuration with path mappings
- [eslint.config.js](mdc:eslint.config.js) - ESLint rules enforcing architecture
- [tamagui.config.ts](mdc:tamagui.config.ts) - UI theme configuration
- [.gitignore](mdc:.gitignore) - Comprehensive ignore patterns

## Entry Points
- [app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx](mdc:app/(tabs)/_layout.tsx) - Tab navigation layout
- [app/(tabs)/index.tsx](mdc:app/(tabs)/index.tsx) - Home screen
- [src/shared/i18n/index.ts](mdc:src/shared/i18n/index.ts) - Internationalization setup

